Text.string: That's all the towers, sugar. Swing by the bar and we'll celebrate. First round's on me.
To the tools of the trade, to bullet and frag. Here's to the Hunters, may they live till they sag!
To the bravest and boldest, Vault Hunters all. We toast to the champions, may they ever stand tall!
To our Vault Hunter hero, who came up with a fix for our COV problem, by wasting those pricks.
Here's to the COV slaughtered, as is their grim fate. Rot in hell, you bastards. Better sooner than late.
Cutting down cultists, slaying all in their path. The Vault Hunters triumph, may all foes fear their wrath!

Hey, sugar. We haven't had the pleasure of meeting yet. I'm Moxxi, and I've got a job for you. Those Calypso Twins live for attention, right? So I say we take it away by turning their own broadcast towers against them.
Hey, sugar. Moxxi here, and I've got a job for you. Those Calypso Twins live for attention, right? So I say we take it away by turning their own broadcast towers against them.
Looks like there's a COV broadcast tower nearby. Let's sabotage it.
Ready to dismantle the COV propaganda network? 'Cause there's a broadcast tower nearby.
There's a broadcast tower nearby. Go take it.
Let's take that broadcast tower away from the COV.
Broadcast tower near you. Let's take it.
Thanks for turnin' that tower to our side, sugar. That should get the Calypsos' attention.
Taking that COV filth off the radio is important. Now we can replace it with MY kind of filth.
That COV propaganda was driving me up the wall. But you've sure got my frequency locked in, sugar.
Ah, the soothing sound of dead air. Well done, sugar. Now, let's give the people somethin' to listen to.
So long, COV radio. I think that deserves a shot on me. Keep this up and I'll upgrade you to a shot off me.
Now they'll have to spread their manure by hand and not over the airwaves.
I'd rather listen to an all-rakk metal band than those propaganda-pushers. Thanks for giving us a moment's reprieve, sugar.
That was music to my ears, Vault Hunter. Play it again sometime, would ya?
Thanks for getting those jerks off the air, Vault Hunter. And now back to our regularly scheduled broadcast.
I owe you one, sugar. If I had to listen to that COV trash for one more minute I was gonna jam cocktail onions in my ears.
It feels good to get those COV nutjobs off the airwaves. Score one for the Raiders.
Time to replace that awful COV racket with the sweet sounds of Crimson.
Goodbye, COV propaganda. Hello, Crimson propaganda.
I've spent plenty of time around bandits and trust me, you don't wanna hear anything they have to say. Thanks for turning them off, and me on.
You sure know how to turn a dial, sugar. That hits the spot.
I've seen what happens when you whip a bandit mob into a frenzy, and it's not pretty. Takin' the COV off the air gives us more room to breathe.
The Calypsos live and breathe for attention. Taking away the mic is sure to get their skivvies in a twist. And not in a good way.
Time to put my boot on the neck of the COV propaganda operation. Let's get Crimson Radio on the air.
